I need to identify the amount of profit an entity retains after all expenses (net profit) and extract 5 sub-items that contribute to this calculation.

Looking at the income statement:

1. The net profit is clearly labeled as "Net Profit" with a value of 146127.58.

2. For the sub-items, I need to choose 5 components that contribute to this calculation:
   - Main Business Revenue: 863371.65 (the starting point)
   - Cost of Goods Sold: 562950.00 (major deduction)
   - Total Expenses: 120192.24 (combined operating expenses)
   - Interest Income: 9066.78 (addition to profit)
   - Tax Expense: 43168.61 (final deduction before net profit)

The calculation is essentially:
Net Profit = Main Business Revenue - Cost of Goods Sold - Total Expenses + Interest Income - Tax Expense
146127.58 = 863371.65 - 562950.00 - 120192.24 + 9066.78 - 43168.61
